## Faster RCNN论文笔记

### 1. Abstract

- Introducing  RPN shares full conv featr enabling cost-free region proposals
- Merging RPN & Fast RCNN by sharing their conv featr—using  “attention”.

### 2. Introduction

##### Region Proposal Methods

Recent advances in OD are driven by the success of region proposal methods

computationally cost has been reduced by sharing conv across proposals

##### Region Proposal Networks

Introducing new RPNs that share conv layers, so cost for proposals is small 

Constructing RPN by adding conv layers on top of conv features that regress region bounds and obj scores.

### 3. RELATED WORK

##### Object Proposals

Widely used proposal methods include grouping super-pixel and sliding window

##### Deep Networks for Object Detection

OD’s accuracy depends on the performace of the region proposal module

Several papers propose using deep nets for predicting object bounding boxes 

- OverFeat using trained FCs  to predict box coordinates
- MultiBox gen. proposals from last FC layer predicts multiple class box

### 4.  FASTER R-CNN

Faster R-CNN is composed of 2 modules: 

- The first is a deep fully convolutional network that proposes regions
- The second  is Fast R-CNN detector that uses the proposed regions
